    <text id="R12540570T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>In this May, 1863, letter, Union General Robert Milroy writes Robert Schenck to
                    suggest a large attack on Staunton to relieve pressure on General Joseph
                    Hooker's Army of the Potomac.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Maj.-Gen. SCHENCK,<lb/> Baltimore, Md.:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1863-05-30">May 30, 1863</date>--<time>10.40 a. m.</time>
                        <name type="place">WINCHESTER, VA.,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>
                <p>Every indication goes to show a tremendous concentration of the rebel forces on
                    Gen. Hooker. Would it not be a splendid diversion in his favor for all our
                    forces in Western Virginia to move at once on Staunton, and all my forces to
                    move up the Valley upon the same point?</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>R. H. MILROY,<lb/> Maj.-Gen.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
